INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('4015', '5', 'Transfer fish to plates. Spoon cucumber relish alongside. garnish with cilantro sprigs.'),
('4016', '1', 'Put the mahimahi fillets in a large, shallow dish.'),
('4016', '2', 'Pour the lemon juice over the fish and season lightly with salt. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.'),
('4016', '3', 'In a very large enameled cast-iron casserole, heat the oil.'),
('4016', '4', 'Add the garlic cloves and cook over moderately high heat until sizzling, about 2 minutes.'),
('4016', '5', 'Add the shallots and cook over moderate heat, stirring until softened, about 3 minutes.'),
('4016', '6', 'Add the chiles and curry leaves and cook for 2 minutes.'),
('4016', '7', 'Add the ginger and lime leaves and cook for 2 minutes.'),
('4016', '8', 'Add the fennel, carrots and curry powder and season lightly with salt. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables begin to soften, about  5 minutes.'),
('4016', '9', 'Add the coconut milk and bring to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat, stirring a few times, until the carrots are tender, about 10 minutes longer.'),
('4016', '10', 'Add the mahimahi and any accumulated juices to the casserole, nestling the fish into the stew. Cover and simmer over low heat, shifting the fish a few times, until it is just cooked, about 15 minutes.'),
('4016', '11', 'Transfer the fillets to a large, deep platter.'),
('4016', '12', 'Pour the sauce over and around the fish.'),
('4016', '13', 'Garnish with the cilantro and serve.'),
('4017', '1', 'Preheat a gas grill to medium-high. If you are using a charcoal grill, build a fire and let it burn down until the coals are glowing red with a moderate coating of white ash.'),
('4017', '2', 'Spread the coals in an even bed. Clean the cooking grate.'),
('4017', '3', 'Cut the mahi-mahi into 16 equal slices.'),
('4017', '4', 'Combine the oil, lime juice, chili powder, cumin, coriander, garlic, and salt. Coat the mahi-mahi with the marinade.'),
('4017', '5', 'Grill the fish on the first side over direct heat until the flesh is firm and well-marked, about 2 minutes. Turn the fish and grill until cooked through, about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes more.'),
('4017', '6', 'Grill the tortillas until they have light grill marks and are heated through, about 15 seconds on the first side. Turn the tortillas and grill them until they just start to bubble, another 15 seconds.'),
('4017', '7', 'Center 2 pieces of grilled fish on each tortilla, and top with the Southwestern Slaw and Chipotle Pico de Gallo.'),
('4017', '8', 'Add a dollop of Mexican Crema, fold in half, and serve immediately.'),
('4017', '9', 'Reprinted with permission from Grilling: Exciting International Flavors from the World''s Premier Culinary College by The Culinary Institute of America 2006 Lebhar-Friedman Books'),
('4018', '1', 'In a large, deep skillet, heat the 1/4 cup of olive oil until shimmering.'),
('4018', '2', 'Add the celery, onion and garlic and cook over moderate heat until just softened, 4 minutes.'),
('4018', '3', 'Add the tomato sauce, wine, vinegar, artichokes, olives, pine nuts, sugar and capers and season with salt and pepper. Simmer until the vegetables are tender and the liquid is reduced, 8 minutes. Stir in the basil and let cool.'),
('4018', '4', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan. Rub the fish with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill over moderately high heat, turning once, until cooked through, about 9 minutes.'),
('4018', '5', 'Transfer the fish to plates, top with the caponata and serve.'),
('4020', '1', 'Mix up the taco seasoning and keep it in a shaker jar with a tight lid.Sprinkle the seasoning over the fish, tossing to coat.Warm the oil in the skillet and add the seasoned fish. Saut, stirring occasionally until the fish is cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes.'),
('4020', '2', 'Transfer cooked fish to a warm bowl and serve with the suggested accompaniments.'),
('4023', '1', 'Chop the reserved chicken and vegetables and mix them all together along with the apple. In a small bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, mustard, parsley, and salt and pepper, to taste. Toss with the chopped chicken mixture. Divide the mixture among the tortillas, wrap up, and enjoy.'),
('4026', '1', 'Grate enough lemon peel to measure2 1/2 teaspoons. Halve lemons. squeezeenough juice to measure 1/4 cup.'),
('4026', '2', 'Mix peel,2 tablespoons juice, mayonnaise, 1/4 cupgreen onion, relish, horseradish, and 2tablespoons dill in bowl. set sauce aside.'),
('4026', '3', 'Grind bread to fine crumbs in processor.'),
('4026', '4', 'Place 1 cup breadcrumbs in medium bowl.'),
('4026', '5', 'Place remaining breadcrumbs in 13x9-inchbaking dish. Using on/off turns, verycoarsely chop fish in processor (do not formpaste).'),
('4026', '6', 'Add fish to breadcrumbs in bowl.gently mix in egg, 1 tablespoon sauce, and1/4 cup green onion. Shape fish mixture intofour 31/2-inch-round cakes. thickly coat withbreadcrumbs in baking dish.'),
('4026', '7', 'Toss coleslaw mix, 3 tablespoons sauce,2 tablespoons lemon juice, and 1 tablespoondill in bowl. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('4026', '8', 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet overmedium heat.'),
('4026', '9', 'Add fish cakes. saute untilcooked through, about 2 minutes per side.'),
('4026', '10', 'Serve fish cakes with slaw and sauce.'),
('4026', '11', 'Bon Appetit'),
('4029', '1', 'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Season the mahi-mahi with salt and pepper. Cook the fillets in the hot oil until the fish is golden brown on each side, and no longer translucent in the center, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('4029', '2', 'Meanwhile, whisk together the sour cream, lime juice, ginger, cumin, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper to taste. set aside. Gently combine the mango, pineapple, avocado, and jalapeno in a bowl.'),
('4029', '3', 'To assemble, place a cooked mahi-mahi fillet into the center of a warmed tortilla.'),
('4029', '4', 'Place a scoop of the mango salsa onto the fish, then drizzle with the sour cream sauce, and finish with a generous pinch of chopped cilantro.'),
('4033', '1', 'Combine wine and mussels in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Cover and cook for 5 minutes or until mussels open. discard any unopened shells.'),
('4033', '2', 'Remove mussels from pan with a slotted spoon, reserving liquid.'),
('4033', '3', 'Remove meat from mussels, and discard shells.'),
('4033', '4', 'Place mussels in a large bowl. Line a sieve with dampened cheesecloth, allowing cheesecloth to extend over edge of sieve.'),
('4033', '5', 'Drain cooking liquid through sieve over a bowl, reserving liquid. discard cheesecloth.'),
('4033', '6', 'Return liquid to pan. bring to a boil.'),
('4033', '7', 'Add shrimp and squid to pan. cook for 4 minutes or until done, stirring occasionally.'),
('4033', '8', 'Remove shrimp and squid with a slotted spoon. discard liquid.'),
('4033', '9', 'Add shrimp and squid to mussels.'),
('4033', '10', 'Combine 1/4 cup lemon juice and next 6 ingredients (through garlic) in a bowl, stirring well with a whisk.'),
('4033', '11', 'Drizzle lemon juice mixture over shrimp mixture, tossing to coat.'),
('4033', '12', 'Combine lettuce and fennel in a large bowl.'),
('4033', '13', 'Add remaining 4 teaspoons lemon juice to fennel mixture, and toss to coat. Arrange fennel mixture on a platter. top with shrimp mixture.'),
('4035', '1', 'To prepare spice mix, combine first 6 ingredients in a spice or coffee grinder. process until finely ground.'),
('4035', '2', 'To prepare fish, combine mahimahi, turmeric, and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a large bowl. toss well.'),
('4035', '3', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4035', '4', 'Add half of fish. cook 5 minutes or until fish is lightly browned and flakes easily when tested with a fork (do not overcook).'),
('4035', '5', 'Remove from pan. Repeat procedure with remaining fish and oil.'),
('4035', '6', 'To prepare sauce, add onion to pan. saut 5 minutes or until tender.'),
('4035', '7', 'Add ginger, garlic, and bay leaf. saut 2 minutes.'),
('4035', '8', 'Add ground spice mix. cook 2 minutes. Stir in water, 1 teaspoon salt, and sugar.'),
('4035', '9', 'Remove pan from heat. gradually stir in yogurt. Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Return fish and accumulated juices to pan. Cook over low heat 5 minutes or just until heated. Discard bay leaf.'),
('4036', '1', 'To prepare Pineapple Salsa, combine pineapple, red and green peppers, cilantro, 1 tablespoon lime juice, red pepper flakes and lime peel in medium bowl.(Pineapple Salsa may be prepared 1 to 2 days ahead and refrigerated.).Preheat broiler.Spray rack of broiler pan with cooking spray.Rinse mahi-mahi and pat dry with paper towels.'),
('4036', '2', 'Place mahi-mahi on rack.'),
('4036', '3', 'Combine remaining 1 tablespoon lime juice and olive oil. brush on mahi-mahi.Broil mahi-mahi, 4 inches from heat, 2 minutes.Turn and brush second side with olive oil mixture. sprinkle with white pepper.Continue to broil 2 minutes or until mahi-mahi flakes easily when tested with fork.'),
('4036', '4', 'Serve with Pineapple Salsa.'),
('4037', '1', 'Mix all ingerdients in salsa together, except mango.Cover and chill overnight.Grill Mahi Mahi on a hot grill, 5 min.each side and season with salt and cracked pepper.'),
('4037', '2', 'Add mango to salsa just before serving and mix well.'),
('4037', '3', 'Place salsa on Mahi Mahi steaks and serve.'),
('4038', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F.'),
('4038', '2', 'Mix dressing, jalapeno and ginger. set aside.  Hold banana leaf with tongs and pass quickly across a stove burner on medium heat several times until banana leaf is pliable.  (Do not overheat or leaf will become brittle.)  Repeat with the remaining leaves.  Line 13x9-inch baking pan with the softened leaves, with ends of leaves extending over sides of pan.'),
('4038', '3', 'Place fish in prepared baking pan. drizzle with the dressing mixture.  Top with the coconut and limes.  Fold  banana leaves over fish.  Top with an empty glass baking dish to hold leaves in place.'),
('4038', '4', 'Bake 20 min. or until fish is cooked through.'),
('4038', '5', 'Serve in baking pan.'),
('4040', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('4040', '2', 'Pat fish dry and combine in a nonreactive bowl with the white wine, lime juice and garlic. Set aside to marinate about 10 to 15 minutes.'),
('4040', '3', 'When fish is ready, remove it from the marinade, pat dry, and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),
('4040', '4', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat. When oil shimmers, place fish skin-side down in skillet. Cook until opaque and firm to touch, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('4040', '5', 'Flake the fish, squeeze one of the lime wedges over the top, and toss to coat. To make a taco, stack 2 tortillas on top of each other and fill with fish, lettuce, salsa, a few avocado slices, and a dollop of sour cream. Repeat to make 6 tacos total.'),
('4044', '1', 'Marinate the Seafood: In a bowl, combine all of the ingredients except the shells and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.'),
('4044', '2', 'Meanwhile, Make the Shrimp Stock: In a large saucepan, cover the shrimp shells with the water.'),
('4044', '3', 'Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer for 45 minutes.'),
('4044', '4', 'Let cool. Strain the stock.'),
('4044', '5', 'Make the Soup: In a large saucepan, melt the butter.'),
('4044', '6', 'Add the flour. whisk over moderately low heat until foamy, about 3 minutes.'),
('4044', '7', 'Add the coconut milk. whisk over high heat until thickened, about 5 minutes.'),
('4044', '8', 'Add the shrimp stock and bring to a simmer. Cover and keep warm.'),
('4044', '9', 'In a large enameled cast-iron casserole, heat 1 tablespoon of the dend oil.'),
('4044', '10', 'Add the onion and a pinch of salt and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until softened, 5 minutes.'),
('4044', '11', 'Add half of the tomatoes and cook until softened, 5 minutes. Stir in the marinated seafood and cook for 2 minutes.'),
('4044', '12', 'Pour in the soup and simmer until the seafood is just cooked, 6 minutes. Stir in the cilantro.'),
('4044', '13', 'Meanwhile, in a small skillet, heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of dend oil.'),
('4044', '14', 'Add the hearts of palm and the remaining tomatoes, season with salt and cook over high heat until warmed through, 1 minute. Spoon the Coconut-Cashew Rice into shallow bowls and ladle the soup on top.'),
('4044', '15', 'Garnish with the hearts of palm and tomatoes and serve.'),
('4045', '1', 'Heat a small nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('4045', '2', 'Add lemon, 1 tablespoon water, 1/2 teaspoon oil, and sugar. cook 3 minutes or until water evaporates and mixture just begins to brown, stirring frequently. Set aside.'),
('4045', '3', 'Place remaining 2 1/2 teaspoons oil in a small microwave-safe bowl, and microwave at high for 10 seconds at a time just until oil is heated. Stir in saffron. let stand 10 minutes.'),
('4045', '4', 'Combine lemon mixture, saffron mixture, chopped parsley, and next 7 ingredients (through garlic) in a large zip-top plastic bag.'),
('4045', '5', 'Add fish to bag, and seal. Marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes, turning occasionally.'),
('4045', '6', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('4045', '7', 'Layer 1 cup onion slices and 2 cups tomato on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.'),
('4045', '8', 'Remove fish from bag, reserving marinade. Top tomato with fish. pour remaining marinade from bag over fish. Cover with remaining 2 cups tomato and remaining 1 cup onion. Cover with foil.'),
('4045', '9', 'Bake at 400 for 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4045', '10', 'Remove from oven.'),
('4045', '11', 'Transfer fish and vegetables to a serving platter.'),
('4045', '12', 'Drizzle remaining liquid over fish.'),
('4045', '13', 'Garnish with cilantro leaves, if desired.'),
('4045', '14', 'Serve immediately.'),
('4046', '1', 'Preheat grill pan or indoor electric grill to high heat. Squeeze juice of 1 lime over fish.'),
('4046', '2', 'Drizzle steaks with a little oil and rub oil into fish to coat. Season steaks with salt and pepper. Cook steaks 5 minutes on each side on hot grill.'),
('4046', '3', 'To assemble salsa, combine all ingredients for salsa in a small bowl.'),
('4046', '4', 'To make couscous, bring broth or water to a boil with curry powder, salt, oil, and raisins.'),
('4046', '5', 'Place couscous in a bowl.'),
('4046', '6', 'Add boiling liquid to bowl and cover.'),
('4046', '7', 'Let couscous stand 10 minutes. Fluff couscous with a fork and combine with scallions, carrot, orange pieces, and almonds.'),
('4046', '8', 'Top fish with salsa and serve with generous portions of curry couscous.'),
('4046', '9', 'Have some gourmet chips on hand for snacking with leftover salsa.'),
('4047', '1', 'In a medium bowl, combine the mangos, bell pepper, green onion, cilantro and jalapeno pepper. Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and lime juice. Stir together then cover and refrigerate until serving to blend the flavors.'),
('4047', '2', 'Soak the plank in water for at least 2 hours, longer if possible.'),
('4047', '3', 'Place the mahi mahi fillets in a shallow dish and coat with teriyaki sauce. Cover, and marinate for at least 1 hour.'),
('4047', '4', 'Prepare a grill for indirect heat. If using charcoal, arrange and light coals under one half of the grill. Sprinkle lemon juice over the fish fillets and season with chipotle seasoning, red pepper flakes and hot pepper sauce.'),
('4047', '5', 'Place the fillets on the plank.'),
('4047', '6', 'Place the plank on the grill over direct heat. Cover and cook for 10 minutes. Move the plank with the fish over to indirect heat (the cooler part of the grill), cover and cook for 10 more minutes or until fish can be flaked with a fork. Top fillets with mango salsa and serve hot.'),
('4048', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('4048', '2', 'Preheat grill to medium-high heat.'),
('4048', '3', 'Place fish in a medium size dish.'),
('4048', '4', 'Whisk together the oil, lime juice, ancho, jalapeno, and cilantro and pour over the fish.'),
('4048', '5', 'Let marinate for 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('4048', '6', 'Remove the fish from the marinade place onto a hot grill, flesh side down. Grill the fish for 4 minutes on the first side and then flip for 30 seconds and remove.'),
('4048', '7', 'Let rest for 5 minutes then flake the fish with a fork.'),
('4048', '8', 'Place the tortillas on the grill and grill for 20 seconds. Divide the fish among the tortillas and garnish with any or all of the garnishes.'),
('4048', '9', 'Preheat grill or use side burners of the grill.'),
('4048', '10', 'Heat oil in medium saucepan, add onions and garlic and cook until soft.'),
('4048', '11', 'Add tomatoes, serrano and jalapeno and cook until tomatoes are soft, about 15 to 20 minutes. Puree the mixture with a hand-held immersion blender until smooth and cook for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.'),
('4048', '12', 'Add the hot sauce, oregano, cilantro and lime juice and season with salt and pepper, to taste.'),
('4049', '1', 'Preheat grill.'),
('4049', '2', 'Combine and whisk together the lime juice, olive oil, garlic, soy sauce, ground ginger, dijon mustard, salt, and pepper.Using aluminum foil, form an open "packet" to allow fish to sit in garlic-lime mixture for easier grilling.Coat bottom of foil with cooking spray or butter to prevent fish from sticking.'),
('4049', '3', 'Place the fish in the packet and brush with about half of the dressing and reserve the rest.'),
('4049', '4', 'Place packet on the grill, and cook to desired temperature, flipping only once.'),
('4049', '5', 'Brush mahi mahi steaks once again with the remaining dressing after flipping.'),
('4050', '1', 'Chop pineapple into small pieces.'),
('4050', '2', 'Combine with salsa, cornstarch, horseradish and honey mustard.Coat both sides of fish with cooking spray.Sprinkle fish evenly with lemon pepper.Preheat large saute pan on medium-high.Cook fish 3 minutes. turn.'),
('4050', '3', 'Add salsa to one side of the pan & stir often to evenly heat.Reduce heat to medium, and simmer 5-6 minutes or until flesh is opaque & separates easily with a fork.'),
('4050', '4', 'Serve fish and sauce over prepared long grain rice.'),
('4051', '1', 'Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.'),
('4051', '2', 'Mix nuts, bread crumbs, flour, and tub margarine.Line a baking sheet with foil and spray with cooking spray. Lay fish on the foil, and sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('4051', '3', 'Bake fish for 7 minutes.'),
('4051', '4', 'Remove from oven, brush with coconut milk, and top with nut mixture. Pat mixture down so that it sticks to the fish. You can fold foil edges around fish to condense toppings.'),
('4051', '5', 'Bake fish for additional 12-16 minutes, or until fish is cooked through and crust is golden brown.'),
('4052', '1', 'In a small bowl, mix garlic, lime juice, cumin, and pepper into a paste.'),
('4052', '2', 'Spread mixture onto fish& let sit for 20 minutes.'),
('4052', '3', 'Heat oil in a large skillet and saute fish over moderate heat for 8 minutes, turning it over halfway through the cooking time.'),
('4052', '4', 'Drain onto paper towels.'),
('4052', '5', 'Serve garnished with lime slices.'),
('4053', '1', 'Preheat oven to 37'),
('4053', '2', 'Lightly grease one or two (you''ll probably need two) baking dishes.Wash and pat dry Mahi Mahi fillets and lay them in a single layer in the baking dishe(s).'),
('4053', '3', 'Drizzle fillets with lemon juice, then melted butter (if using it). Sprinkle evenly with the ginger, salt, pepper, and paprika.'),
('4053', '4', 'Place an orange slice over each fillet.Evenly pour the crushed pineapple over all the fillets.'),
('4053', '5', 'Bake at 375 for about 20-30 minutes or until fillets are opaque. do not overbake.'),
('4054', '1', 'Quarter dried mushrooms and chop apricots'),
('4054', '2', 'Place quartered mushrooms and apricots in a bowl and pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over. let stand for 15 minutes. strain, reserving liquid'),
('4054', '3', 'To the strained liquid add coriander, lime zest and juice, salt and pepper to taste'),
('4054', '4', 'Reconstitute enough instant powdered milk to add to the strained liquid to make 2 cups, (about 1 cup). stir and set aside'),
('4054', '5', 'Cut the Mahi Mahi fillet down the middle to make two steaks'),
('4054', '6', 'In a nonstick, deep frypan, sprayed with veggie spray, over medium high heat, saute quartered mushrooms, chopped apricots and shallots for 4 minutes'),
('4054', '7', 'Add Mahi Mahi fillets, skin side up, cook for 1 minute'),
('4054', '8', 'Add reserved liquid mixture, bring to simmer and simmer for 8 minutes or until fish flakes'),
('4054', '9', 'Remove fish and place on platter skin side down and keep warm'),
('4054', '10', 'Make a slurry of the cornstarch and cold water, add to frypan, stir and bring to boil, cook for 2 minutes or until liquid thickens'),
('4054', '11', 'Pour thickened mushroom/apricot sauce over Mahi Mahi fillets and serve'),
('4055', '1', 'Heat olive oil over medium heat in saute pan.'),
('4055', '2', 'Saute sliced onions in the oil for about 8 minutes or until tender.'),
('4055', '3', 'Add tomatoes, parsley, white wine, tomato paste, garlic, 1/4 tsp salt, and 1/4 tsp pepper. Simmer for 5 minutes. Set mixture aside.Lightly grease a rack, and line a broiler pan with aluminum foil.'),
('4055', '4', 'Place rack in broiler pan.'),
('4055', '5', 'Place fish, in a single layer, on the rack. Sprinkle with the remaining salt and pepper. Broil fish about 5 inches from heat for about 8 minutes, or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.Spoon the onion-tomato mixture evenly onto a platter.'),
('4055', '6', 'Place the broiled fish on top of the onion-tomato mixture.Sprinkle with crumbled feta, and garnish with lemon slices.'),
('4056', '1', 'Whisk yogurt, 2 teaspoons ginger, garlic, curry powder, cumin, and cayenne pepper in medium bowl to blend.'),
('4056', '2', 'Add fish and turn to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, turning fish occasionally.'),
('4056', '3', 'Mix cucumber, vinegar, chopped cilantro, and remaining 2 teaspoons ginger in small bowl. Season lightly to taste with pepper. (Relish can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally.)'),
('4056', '4', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat).'),
('4056', '5', 'Brush grill rack with olive oil. Scrape off excess yogurt marinade from fish. sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Grill fish until just opaque in center, about 6 minutes per side.'),
('4056', '6', 'Transfer fish to plates. Spoon cucumber relish alongside. garnish with cilantro sprigs.'),
('4056', '7', '*Also known as sushi vinegar. available at Asian markets and in the Asian foods section of most supermarkets.'),
('4056', '8', 'Per serving (for halibut steaks): calories, 200. total fat, 4 g. saturated fat, 1 g. cholesterol, 64 mg. fiber, 0'),
('4056', '9', 'Bon Appetit'),
('4057', '1', 'To seed the tomatoes for the salsa simply cut the tomato in half and squeeze out the juice and seeds. The juice tends to be a bit acidic and the seeds are bitter (doesnt make a yummy salsa). The amount of sugar you need varies because it depends on how ripe and sweet your tomatoes are. If its tomato season I would say that you do not need any sugar. But if theyre beefsteak tomatoes from your super market, you definitely need sugar.Marinate the fish in garlic, lime juice, hot sauce, oil, and salt and pepper for about 30 minutes before you start cooking. While its marinating heat up your grill. If you dont have a grill (indoor or outdoor) you can broil the fish or pan sear.While the fish is marinating shred your cabbage and set aside. Now all of your condiments are done and ready to go. All you need to do is cook the fish.If you have a grill pan, make sure it is extremely hot before cooking fish. Even though the marinade has salt and pepper in it, once the fish is on the pan I would season again. Cook on one side for about 3 minutes and flip and cook for another 3 minutes. Make sure youve got good grill marks (flavor). When you turn the fish the first time, baste it with left over marinade.Once fish is cooked and has cooled down slightly, flake the fish with your fingers or a fork.'),
('4057', '2', 'Heat up tortillas in oven or microwave and eat!'),
('4058', '1', 'Butterfly cut the mahi-mahi fillets so that they are no more than 1/3 to 1/2 inches (80 to 125 mm) thick.In a small bowl combine the red wine vinegar, honey, garlic, and hoisin sauce. Stir until uniform.'),
('4058', '2', 'Place both the fish and sauce in a large bag and marinate in the fridge for no more than 20 minutes, making sure to coat the fillets evenly. *Marinating for longer than 20 minutes will start to break down the proteins in the fish. Trust me, you want to avoid that.When the fillets are done marinating remove them from the bag and set them aside for now. Reserve the marinade in the bag or a small bowl, you''ll use it later.'),
('4058', '3', 'Heat a medium sized skillet or wok on medium-high heat for 30 seconds (or until a drop of water will instantly boil when added to the pan).'),
('4058', '4', 'Add the olive oil and coat the pan evenly.As soon as the pan''s hot and coated add the fillets. Then sprinkle half of the salt, black pepper, and ginger powder onto the fillets, making sure to cover as much of the meat as possible.'),
('4058', '5', 'Let the fillets cook undisturbed for about 30 seconds or until you notice the edges of the meat beginning to whiten.Cook the fillets until their bottom sides start to caramelize and turn a light golden color (1-2 minutes). flip.Sprinkle the remaining salt, black pepper, and ginger powder onto the fillets and continue cooking until each side is golden and each fillet flakes (2-4 minutes, depending on thickness).'),
('4058', '6', 'Remove the fillets to a serving plate and cover.'),
('4058', '7', 'Add the reserved marinade to the pan and simmer on low heat until the resulting glaze turns a light golden-brown (1-3 minutes). *Make sure to scrape the bottom of the pan to add the fillet drippings to the glaze.Spoon the glaze over each fillet and serve.'),
('4059', '1', 'Add all ingredients except fish in a large resealable plastic bag and mix well.'),
('4059', '2', 'Add fish and refrigerate to marinate for 15 minutes.'),
('4059', '3', 'Remove salmon from marinade and discard marinade.Grill on a greased grill rack over medium-high heat 5-6 per side for slightly rare salmon or cook until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('4060', '1', 'Combine all the ingredients in a 2-cup measuring cup and whisk until smooth. Refrigerate up to 4 hours until ready to use.    To make the tacos:    In a small bowl, combine the ancho powder, cumin, garlic, salt, and pepper and stir to mix.'),
('4060', '2', 'Add the oil and whisk until a loose paste is formed. Rub the fish with the spice paste and let marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes and up to 4 hours.'),
('4060', '3', 'Light a charcoal fire or preheat your gas grill on high. Oil the grills cooking surface.'),
('4060', '4', 'Let the coals burn down to a medium-hot fire or adjust the gas grill burners to medium-high.    Grill the fish until just cooked through, 3 to 4 minutes per side.'),
('4060', '5', 'Transfer to a cutting board and coarsely chop.    Divide the tortillas into 2 stacks and wrap each in aluminum foil.'),
('4060', '6', 'Place on the grill until heated through, about 5 minutes.    In a large bowl, combine the green and red cabbage.    To assemble the tacos, take 2 tortillas, top it with chunks of fish, a dollop of the sauce, a spoonful of the Pico de Gallo, and some of the cabbage. Squeeze a wedge of lime over the filling, fold the tortillas, and eat.'),
('4061', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a large oven proof skillet over medium high heat.Preheat oven to 375 degrees.Season both sides of fish with salt and pepper.Dredge only one side of each fillet in the cilantro.'),
('4061', '2', 'Place fish, cilantro side down, into the hot olive oil, being careful not to crowd the pan.Cook until cilantro is crisp, checking often not to burn. (I check after 1 minute, then every 30 seconds after that.).Turn fish over, then place in preheated oven.'),
('4061', '3', 'Bake for 3-5 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.If you do not have a large oven proof skillet, you can cook fish a couple of fillets at a time, then transfer to a baking dish to finish cooking. You can use less oil or nonstick spray if using a nonstick pan, just remember to add more before adding more fish.'),
('4061', '4', 'Add extra cooking time since the dish is not preheated.'),
('4062', '1', 'Mix all ingredients together except for fish. Spoon mixture over fish.'),
('4062', '2', 'Place fish into shallow pan (sprayed heavily with cooking spray) and sautee with onions if desired for about 3-5 minutes on the first side and 2-3 minutes on the second side.'),
('4062', '3', 'Add more of the syrup mixture if you want.Best served with rice.***Can also marinate fish for a few hours for maximum flavor.'),
('4063', '1', 'Place fish in medium glass dish or bowl. sprinkle with sea salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),
('4063', '2', 'Add lime juice, lemon juice, and sugar and toss. Cover and chill until fish turns white and no longer looks raw, tossing occasionally, at least 4 hours and up to 6 hours.'),
('4063', '3', 'Strain fish, discarding marinade.'),
('4063', '4', 'Placeceviche in large bowl. add tomatoes, redonion, pickled jalapenos, 1 tablespoon liquid from jar, and olive oil and toss to blend. DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 hours ahead. Cover and chill.'),
('4063', '5', 'Add lettuce, avocado, and cilantro to ceviche mixture and toss. Fill taco shells with ceviche mixture. Top each taco with large spoonful of salsa and serve.'),
('4064', '1', 'For the salsa: Peel the mango and cut into 1/4 inch diced pieces.Put mango pieces in a small bowl with the remaining salsa ingredients. stir to combine.Cover bowl with saran wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.For the marinade: In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, sweet sake, vegetable oil, light brown sugar, fresh ginger, and minced garlic. set aside.'),
('4064', '2', 'Place the mahi mahi fillets in a large zip-lock plastic bag.'),
('4064', '3', 'Pour marinade into bag. press the air out of the bag and seal tightly.Turn/shake the bag to coat fillets with marinade.Refrigerate for 20-30 minutes.Take fillets out of bag and throw away marinade.'),
('4064', '4', 'Brush or spray both sides of fillets with vegetable oil.Grill over high heat until fish is opaque throughout, 8 to 10 minutes, turning once halfway through grilling time.'),
('4064', '5', 'Serve warm with salsa.'),
('4065', '1', 'Combine wine, scallions, garlic, juice, brown sugar, and salt.Bring the mixture to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.Marinate steaks for 60 minutes.Grill or broil steaks, brushing with marinade.'),
('4066', '1', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('4066', '2', 'Cut Mahi Mahi into 1" wide pieces and place pieces in a single layer in a 13" x 9" baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped macadamia nuts on top of Mahi Mahi.'),
('4066', '3', 'Pour coconut milk over top.'),
('4066', '4', 'Bake at 350 for about 18 minutes or until opaque.Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup nuts just before serving.'),
('4067', '1', 'FISH: Stir together the spices and toss with the fish in the bowl or the zipper bag. Set aside.'),
('4067', '2', 'SLAW: In the serving bowl, toss together the sliced cabbage and onions. Measure the cider vinegar in the measuring cup and add the sour cream and salt. Stir until thoroughly mixed, then pour over the cabbage and onions, and stir until the vegetables are evenly coated.'),
('4067', '3', 'SALSA: In the serving bowl, toss together the mango, avocado, jalapeo, onion, and cilantro. Squeeze the limes over the bowl and stir gently.'),
('4072', '1', 'Combine shallots, cilantro, lime juice, olive oil, salt and pepper in a medium bowl.'),
('4072', '2', 'Pour over Mahi Mahi.Grill, covered with grill lid, on a grill rack coated with nonstick cooking spray over medium-high heat 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.'),
('4072', '3', 'Garnish with fresh cilantro if desired.'),
('4073', '1', 'In a skillet melt 1 Tbs of butter over medium heat, add garlic, and saut ''til tender (watch carefully so that it doesn''t burn!).'),
('4073', '2', 'Remove from heat and stir in teriyaki sauce, lemon juice, honey and sesame seeds.'),
('4073', '3', 'Let cool a few minutes then pour over fish and marinate 30 minutes in refrigerator.'),
('4073', '4', 'Heat remaining Tbs of butter in skillet over medium heat.'),
('4073', '5', 'Remove fish from marinade and add to pan, sauting 4-5 minutes per side and basting with marinade.Note: I like to toast the sesame seeds before adding them to the mixture for a more pronounced flavor.'),
('4076', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking pan with aluminum foil.'),
('4076', '2', 'Arrange the mahi mahi fillets in the prepared baking pan.'),
('4076', '3', 'Pour lemon juice over the fillets, and sprinkle with thyme and basil. Top each fillet with pineapple.'),
('4076', '4', 'Pour milk into the pan, not directly on the fish.'),
('4076', '5', 'Bake 25 minutes in the preheated oven, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('4077', '1', 'In a 1 gallon zipper bag, combine all ingredients except fish. Squish to combine.'),
('4077', '2', 'Add mahi and seal, refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.OAMC - squeeze all air out of zipper bag, or seal in a vacuum sealer and store in the freezer. Defrost and grill, following instructions below.Spray grill with non-stick cooking spray, the preheat to 475F Cook fillets about 4 minutes on the first side, then turn and cook another 2-3 minutes, depending on thickness. Trust yourself on the grill, based on the thickness of your fillets - don''t blindly use my timing! An overcooked fish is a sad fish.'),
('4079', '1', 'Very thinly slice onion crosswise into rings with slicer. Set slicer aside.'),
('4079', '2', 'Heat vinegar, sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a small heavy nonreactive saucepan until sugar has dissolved.'),
('4079', '3', 'Remove from heat and stir in onion, then let stand until ready to use (about 25 minutes).'),
('4079', '4', 'Meanwhile, stir 1/4 cup lime juice together with cilantro, oil, and 1/2 teaspoon salt.'),
('4079', '5', 'Add fish and toss to coat, then marinate at room temperature 15 minutes.'),
('4079', '6', 'Whisk together mayonnaise, crema, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and remaining 3 tablespoons lime juice to make sauce.'),
('4079', '7', 'Preheat a gas grill with burners on high, covered, 10 minutes, then reduce heat to medium-high.'),
('4079', '8', 'Thread each piece of fish onto a skewer (discard marinade). Wrap exposed part of each skewer in heavy-duty foil to protect it from charring.'),
('4079', '9', 'Wrap tortillas in 2 foil packages and warm on grill, turning once, about 3 minutes total.'),
('4079', '10', 'Oil grill rack, then grill fish, covered, turning once, until opaque and just cooked through (for mahimahi), about 6 minutes total. or until just pink in center (for tuna), about 4 minutes.'),
('4079', '11', 'Very thinly slice radishes with slicer. Halve, pit, and peel avocados, then cut into 1/2-inch-thick slices.'),
('4079', '12', 'Drain onions.'),
('4079', '13', 'Serve fish with tortillas, crema sauce, onions, and remaining toppings.'),
('4079', '14', 'Cooks'' note'),
('4079', '15', 'If you aren''t able to grill outdoors, cook fish in a lightly oiled large (2-burner) ridged grill pan. Warm tortillas in foil packages in grill pan 2 to 3 minutes or in a 300F oven 10 minutes.'),
('4080', '1', 'Cut fillets into 2 inch chunks and drizzle with the lemon juice.'),
('4080', '2', 'Pour the beer into the bottom of a saucepan (if using fresh lemon juice, toss the leftover lemon rind in with beer) and place a collapsible vegetable steamer over the beer.Bring the beer to a boil, place the fish chunks in the steamer, cover and steam for 5 to 10 minutes, dependent upon the thickness of the fish.The fish will be rubbery if it is overcooked.Meanwhile, heat the butter with the garlic and salt (I heat it slowly until the garlic is no longer raw).'),
('4080', '3', 'Remove the fish from the steamer and discard the beer/liquid/rind.'),
('4080', '4', 'Serve the fish chunks with the garlic butter dipping sauce.'),
('4081', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350F.'),
('4081', '2', 'Whisk together olive oil and lemon juice in bowl big enough to dip fish into.'),
('4081', '3', 'Mix breadcrumbs, parmesan, dill, rosemary and salt and pepper in another bowl of similar size.Dip each filet in olive oil mixture, then coat with breadcrumb mixture and place in 9x13 inch glass dish.Top each filet with 2-3 dollops butter.'),
('4081', '4', 'Bake for about 15 min or until fish flakes easily with fork.'),
('4082', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375 deg F.'),
('4082', '2', 'Heat butter in small skillet on medium heat.'),
('4082', '3', 'Add garlic and heat for 1 minute.'),
('4082', '4', 'Add honey, worcestershire and mustard, cook for an additional minute.'),
('4082', '5', 'Add lemon juice and allow to cool in refrigerator for 10 minutes, or until mixture is thick.Chop scallions and basil.'),
('4082', '6', 'Cut fish into 2oz portions.Pinch a piece of foil so that it has four raised edges to trap the sauce.Arrange fish on oiled/greased aluminum foil.'),
('4082', '7', 'Spread all of sauce mixture over top of each portion.Top sparingly with basil and scalions.Sprinkle salt and pepper.Roast in oven for 10-15 minutes, depending on thickness of fish (15 minutes per inch thickness for fully cooked), or until desired. If using Ahi, I prefer to cook for 10 minites to allow inside to remain raw.'),
('4082', '8', 'Pour excess baked sauce over fish.'),
('4083', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('4083', '2', 'Heat grill pan over medium high heat or preheat outdoor grill.'),
('4083', '3', 'Combine the juice and zest of 2 lemons, oregano, parsley, 2 cloves garlic, olive oil and add fish, turn to coat and season with salt and pepper.'),
('4083', '4', 'Wrap tortillas in foil and place in warm oven or directly on grill to soften and warm through.'),
('4083', '5', 'Shred romaine lettuce and combine with sliced onions.'),
('4083', '6', 'Slice hot peppers and reserve.'),
('4083', '7', 'Combine red peppers and yogurt in food processor.'),
('4083', '8', 'Add cumin, 1 clove garlic, zest and juice of remaining1 lemon, cucumber and process until smooth, transfer to a bowl.'),
('4083', '9', 'Grill fish 6 to 7 minutes until firm and cooked through then cut into cubes.'),
('4083', '10', 'Serve fish to wrap in soft tortillas with lettuce, onions, hot peppers and sauce.'),
('4084', '1', 'Mix together the first part.Puree to dust or small chunks the second part.whisk together the third part.Put each in a separate bowl.Dip the fish in Flour, egg and nuts and fry.'),
('4085', '1', 'Mix equal parts Parmeasan cheese, Dijon mustard, and mayonnaise.Broil fish.At end of cooking time (depends on thickness of fish), spread mixture evenly over fish and return to broiler.Broil for one to two more minutes or till mixture puffs and browns.'),
('4086', '1', 'Mix first four ingredients together to make sauce, place in refrigerator.'),
('4086', '2', 'Whisk flour, salt, pepper and cumin together in a mixing bowl.Slowly pour in beer while whisking until a smooth batter is formed.Allow this to stand about 15 minutes.Sprinkle fish strips with salt and pepper then squeeze lime juice over each strip.Allow this to stand 15 minutes.'),
('4086', '3', 'Heat oven to 200 F, wrap tortillas in aluminum foil and place in oven.'),
('4086', '4', 'Heat oil (about an inch deep) in large skillet over medium heat.'),
('4086', '5', 'Place fish in batter and thoroughly coat.Fry fish in oil until golden, (about 5 minutes).'),
('4086', '6', 'Place fish on baking sheet lined with paper towel and put in oven until all the fish is fried.Fill each tortilla with a couple fish strips, top with sauce, cabbage, and tomato.'),
('4086', '7', 'Serve with a wedge of lime and I like to put some Tapatio on the taco.'),
('4087', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375F.Rinse the fish fillets, pat dry and set aside.In a food processor, briefly whirl the pineapple, lemon peel, lemon, chile, bell peppers, scallions, ginger and Tabasco till the chutney has a confetti-like appearance.'),
('4087', '2', 'Add reserved juice if chutney seems too dry.'),
('4087', '3', 'Add salt to taste.Arrange the fish in a lightly oiled baking dish.Grill the fish till tender and cooked through and serve topped with chutney.Alternatively: Top with chutney and bake, covered, for 20-25 minutes, till fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('4087', '4', 'Garnish with lemon wedges.'),
('4088', '1', 'Arrange salad bar ingredients in serving dishes and bowls as you prep them: romaine, baby mixed greens, bean sprouts, daikon radishes, carrots, scallions, cucumbers, tomatoes, red onions, mint leaves, basil leaves, nuts and sweet almond or anise "croutons".'),
('4088', '2', 'Heat a grill pan over medium high heat.'),
('4088', '3', 'Combine soy and oil in a shallow dish.'),
('4088', '4', 'Add chicken and turn to coat. Season chicken with salt and pepper.'),
('4088', '5', 'Drizzle fish with oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill chicken 3 minutes on each side.'),
('4088', '6', 'Cut chicken into strips on an angle and pile onto a serving plate. Grill fish 4 to 5 minutes on each side, until opaque. Squeeze lime over the fish and break into chunks as you transfer it to a serving plate.'),
('4088', '7', 'Combine all ingredients, except oil, for peanut dressing in a blender. Blend for 30 seconds, then open lid and continue dressing by streaming in oil.'),
('4088', '8', 'Transfer dressing to a serving dish and sprinkle the dressing with a spoonful of nuts from your salad bar to garnish the dish.'),
('4088', '9', 'For garlic dressing, whisk vinegar, jelly, garlic, black pepper and chili oil together. Stream in vegetable oil while continuing to whisk. When the oil is incorporated, transfer dressing to a small dish to serve.'),
('4089', '1', 'Cut the fish into pieces that will fit well into the taco after they are fried. I usually cut mine about 1 inch by 1 inch by 3 inches.'),
('4090', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees.Rinse fish and pat dry.Arrange fish in an oiled oven proof dish.'),
('4090', '2', 'Heat oil in a skillet.Drop in onion slices, and saute 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('4090', '3', 'Add tomatoes, olives, pine nuts, raisins, capers, garlic, and pepper sauce.Cook 5 minutes over medium-low heat, stirring now and then.Spoon sauce over fish, cover with foil, and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes evenly.'),
('4091', '1', 'Brush fillets with canola oil and sprinkle evenly both sides, with jerk rub seasoning.*Use 1 teaspoons seasoning per side per each fillet. More or less to taste.Rub into fish evenly to coat.'),
('4091', '2', 'Place fillets on hot grill and grill 3-5 minutes per side or til done and flakes easily with a fork.Warm tortillas on grill.'),
('4091', '3', 'Cut fillets into chunks, or coarsely shred with a fork.Divide fish evenly onto 8 warmed tortillas.Top each with fruit salsa, a slice of avocado, shredded cabbage, jicama, and top with lime sour cream.Lime sour cream:.'),
('4091', '4', 'Mix sour cream, lime juice and zest in small bowl.'),
('4091', '5', 'Garnish with additional cilantro if desired.*Note: If scotch bonnet or habanero peppers are too hot for your tastebuds, a red jalapeno can be substituted! They are actually quite mild.Enjoy!'),
('4091', '6', 'Serves 4, two tacos apiece!The seasoning is: Dry Jerk Seasoning by susie cooks, recipe #229443.'),
('4093', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 450 degrees.'),
('4093', '2', 'Heat the oil in a skillet over high heat until hot but not smoking.'),
('4093', '3', 'Add the monkfish, shaking the pan as you add the fish to prevent sticking. Sear the fish on one side until golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('4093', '4', 'Transfer to the oven and roast until opaque and firm to the touch, about 8 minutes.'),
('4093', '5', 'Transfer the fish to a warm plate and set aside.'),
('4093', '6', 'Place the skillet over medium heat and add the wine or vermouth and 1/4 cup water, scraping the browned bits from the pan.'),
('4093', '7', 'Add the Chunky Cipolline Tomato Compote to the skillet and cook until heated through.'),
('4093', '8', 'Season to taste with salt and pepper. Spoon the compote among 4 dinner plates, arrange a piece of the monkfish over the compote, and serve.'),
('4098', '1', 'MAKE PORTIONS BY DIVIDING THE MONKFISH IN TWO 100 GRAM SECTIONS. COOK THE WHOLE POTATOES IN THE FISH STOCK. BLANCH THE GREEN BEANS AND SAUTE WITH THE POTATOES.SCORE THE FISH AND ADD TO THE VEGETABLES PAN, BASTE WITH THE SAUCE AND HEAT EVERYTHING TOGETHER. FOR THE SAUCE, FRY A TABLESPOON OF THE PASTE BASE, BASTE WITH THE FISH STOCK AND REMOVE FROM HEAT, ADD THE PEAR PUREE AND GARLIC MAYONNAISE, CONTINUE BEATING WITH A WHISK SO THE INGREDIENTS DO NOT SEPARATE, STRAIN AND RESERVE.FOR THE GARLIC MAYONNAISE, MAKE A PUREE OF ROASTED GARLIC WITH THE EGG YOLKS AND DRIZZLE IN THE OIL,  BAKE THE PEARS WITH THE SKIN ON, REMOVE THE MEAT OF THE FRUIT AND CRUSH IT, BASTE IT WITH THE FISH STOCK AND BLEND WITH THE GARLIC MAYONNAISE.SOFREGIT - MINCE THE ONION AND STEAM IT COVERED, THEN INCREASE THE HEAT AND ADD THE GARLIC, PAPRIKA AND TOMATO (SEEDED AND MINCED) IN THAT ORDER. COOK FOR ABOUT 4 HOURS UNTIL IT BECOMES A COMPOTE.'),
('4100', '1', 'Rinse the monkfish and pat dry. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('4100', '2', 'Arrange half of the prosciutto slices on a work surface, overlapping them to make a rectangle large enough to enclose one of the monkfish tails (use enough prosciutto to enclose the monkfish securely. you may have a couple of slices left over). Lay the fish in the center and fold the prosciutto up and around it to make a tight roulade. If necessary, secure with butchers twine or toothpicks. Repeat with the second tail.'),
('4100', '3', 'Set seam side down on a plate and refrigerate for 1 hour.'),
('4100', '4', 'Preheat a gas grill or prepare a fire in a charcoal grill.'),
('4100', '5', 'Place a piastra  on the grill to preheat.'),
('4100', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a large pot, bring 6 quarts of water to a boil and add 2 tablespoons salt. Set up an ice water bath.'),
('4100', '7', 'Drop the fregola into the boiling water and cook until just al dente.'),
('4100', '8', 'Drain and immediately refresh in the ice bath. when it is cool, drain the fregola extremely well.'),
('4100', '9', 'In a large bowl, toss the fregola with the pesto and red peppers. Set aside.'),
('4100', '10', 'Brush each prosciutto-wrapped tail with 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.'),
('4100', '11', 'Place on the piastra and cook for 6 minutes, unmoved. Gently roll each one over 90 degrees and cook for 4 minutes. Repeat twice, for a total cooking time of about 18 minutes. the internal temperature should be about 150F in the thickest part of the fish.'),
('4100', '12', 'Transfer to a platter and allow to rest for 10 minutes.'),
('4100', '13', 'Cut the tails into -inch slices and arrange nicely on top of the fregola.'),
('4100', '14', 'Drizzle with the remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil, sprinkle with the pine nuts, and serve.'),
('4100', '15', 'var article'),
('4100', '16', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('4100', '17', 'article'),
('4100', '18', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('4101', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('4101', '2', 'In a large skillet, warm 1/4 cup of the olive oil.'),
('4101', '3', 'Add the sliced garlic and cook slowly over very low heat, shaking the skillet, until the garlic is deep golden, 15 minutes.'),
('4101', '4', 'Remove about 1/4 cup of garlic slices to a plate and reserve.'),
('4101', '5', 'Add the paprika to the garlic in the skillet and cook for 1 minute.'),
('4101', '6', 'Add the tomatoes and cook over moderately high heat for 1 minute.'),
('4101', '7', 'Add the water and simmer until the sauce has reduced to 1 1/2 cups, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('4101', '8', 'In a very large skillet, heat the 3 tablespoons of olive oil. Season the fish with salt and pepper. Cook over high heat until browned on the bottom, 2 minutes. Turn the fish, transfer to the oven, and roast until just cooked through, 15 minutes.'),
('4101', '9', 'Transfer the fish to a large, warmed platter.'),
('4101', '10', 'Pour any juices from the skillet into the sauce and simmer for 2 minutes. Spoon the sauce onto plates and set the fish on top. Scatter the fried garlic over the fish and serve right away.'),
('4104', '1', 'If you have time, soak the kombu in the water for at least one hour to make the stock for the nabe. If not, you can simmer the water and kombu for about ten minutes.'),
('4104', '2', 'Remove the kombu from the water, then add the mirin, sake kasu, miso and monkfish along with any tougher vegetables like carrot, gobo, and Tokyo negi. Simmer all the ingredients together until the monkfish and vegetables are tender (about 20-30 minutes).When you''re ready to eat, just add the rest of the vegetables and bring it back to a simmer until they''re cooked. Top with the mitsuba and serve with rice.'),
('4107', '1', 'Heat oven to 45'),
('4107', '2', 'Toss eggplant, zucchini, bell pepper and onion with 2 tsp oil in a bowl.'),
('4107', '3', 'Add thyme. season with salt and pepper and toss again. Coat a shallow baking pan with cooking spray. Arrange vegetables on pan and roast until tender, about 20 minutes. Stir in garlic and marinara. Cover loosely with foil and roast 10 minutes more.'),
('4107', '4', 'Remove pan from oven. Stir in chopped basil. Rub fillets with remaining 2 tsp oil. season with salt and pepper. Nestle fish in vegetables. cover loosely with foil.'),
('4107', '5', 'Bake until fish is just cooked through, about 10 minutes. Top with basil leaves and capers.'),
('4107', '6', 'Heat oven to 45'),
('4107', '7', 'Toss eggplant, zucchini, bell pepper and onion with 2 tsp oil in a bowl.'),
('4107', '8', 'Add thyme. season with salt and pepper and toss again. Coat a shallow baking pan with cooking spray. Arrange vegetables on pan and roast until tender, about 20 minutes. Stir in garlic and marinara. Cover loosely with foil and roast 10 minutes more.'),
('4107', '9', 'Remove pan from oven. Stir in chopped basil. Rub fillets with remaining 2 tsp oil. season with salt and pepper. Nestle fish in vegetables. cover loosely with foil.'),
('4107', '10', 'Bake until fish is just cooked through, about 10 minutes. Top with basil leaves and capers.'),
('4109', '1', 'Bake for 13 to 15 minutes at 210C (410F) in a preheated oven.Monkfish on Wild Rocket & Pomegranate Seeds'),
('4109', '2', 'Recipe source: Kochen mit Kerner, Tim Mlzer (adapted)Required time: prep.: 20 min., baking time: 12-15 min..Ingredients ('),
('4112', '1', 'One day before serving, marinate the fish: place the monkfish in a dish and pour the olive oil over it. Cover with the herbs and garlic. Cover the dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.'),
('4112', '2', 'For the vegetables, preheat the oven to 550 degrees. Sprinkle both sides of the portobellos generously with salt and pepper.'),
('4112', '3', 'Put them in a roasting pan and scatter the thyme and garlic over them.'),
('4112', '4', 'Drizzle with 3 tablespoons of olive oil. Roast until the mushrooms are soft, sliding a spatula underneath them from time to time, about 12 minutes. Quarter the mushrooms and set them aside.'),
('4112', '5', 'Meanwhile, bring a pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('4112', '6', 'Cut off the asparagus tips and reserve the stalks for another use. Blanch the tips until just tender, about 1 minutes.'),
('4112', '7', 'Drain and refresh under cold running water.'),
('4112', '8', 'Drain again and set aside.'),
('4112', '9', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a 10-inch nonstick skillet over high heat.'),
('4112', '10', 'Add half the tomato slices in a single layer. Saut until the slices are browned on the bottom, about 2 minutes. Turn and brown the other side, about 1 minute more. Set the tomatoes aside and wipe out the skillet.'),
('4112', '11', 'Add the remaining tablespoon of oil and Saut the remaining tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper and set aside. (The vegetables can be made up to 1 day ahead. cover and refrigerate.)'),
('4112', '12', 'For the sauce, heat the com oil in a medium saucepan over high heat.'),
('4112', '13', 'Add the beef and brown it on all sides, about 2 minutes.'),
('4112', '14', 'Pour off the fat.'),
('4112', '15', 'Add the brandy and deglaze the pan, scraping up any bits from the bottom.'),
('4112', '16', 'Add 2 tablespoons of butter and lower the heat to medium.'),
('4112', '17', 'Add the green peppercorns, cream, and demi-glace. Season with salt and pepper, if needed, depending on the spiciness of the peppercorns. Simmer for 8 minutes.'),
('4112', '18', 'Whisk in the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter, and simmer until the sauce is thick, about 7 minutes longer.'),
('4112', '19', 'Remove and discard the beef. (The sauce can be made up to 2 hours ahead. refrigerate.)'),
('4112', '20', 'Start a large charcoal fire or preheat an indoor grill. When very hot, place the slate on the grill.'),
('4112', '21', 'Heat the slate until very hot, about 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees. Season the monkfish on both sides with salt and pepper.'),
('4112', '22', 'Pour half the oil from the marinade over the slate and lay the monkfish on top.'),
('4112', '23', 'Place the herbs and garlic back over the fish. After a few minutes, run a spatula under the fish to prevent it from sticking.'),
('4112', '24', 'Grill until the fish is well browned on the bottom, about 10 minutes.'),
('4112', '25', 'Pour the remaining oil from the marinade on the slate, turn the fish over, and put the herbs and garlic back on top. Grill for 10 to 12 minutes, until a metal skewer can be easily inserted into the fish and feels hot when touched to your lip.'),
('4112', '26', 'Meanwhile, alternate pieces of portobello and tomato in a ring around the platter, leaving room in the center for the fish. Lay the asparagus tips over the mushrooms and tomatoes.'),
('4112', '27', 'Place the platter in the oven just to reheat the vegetables, about 2 minutes. Reheat the sauce.'),
('4112', '28', 'Place the monkfish in the center of the platter, covered with the herbs.'),
('4112', '29', 'Serve immediately, carving the fish at the table into -inch-wide slices. Pass the sauce separately. Leave the slate on the grill until cool enough to handle.'),
('4112', '30', 'var article'),
('4112', '31', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('4112', '32', 'article'),
('4112', '33', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('4113', '1', 'Light a gas or charcoal grill. Alternately thread 4 slices of the chorizo, 4 of the cherry tomatoes, 3 or 4 chunks of the monkfish and 3 pieces of the red onion onto each of four 12-inch metal skewers.'),
('4113', '2', 'Brush the monkfish and chorizo kebabs with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.'),
('4113', '3', 'Grill the kebabs over a medium-hot fire, turning once, until lightly charred and the fish is cooked through, about 4 minutes per side.'),
('4113', '4', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil with the lemon juice and cilantro.'),
('4113', '5', 'Transfer the kebabs to a platter and drizzle with the cilantro dressing. Grill the baguette halves, cut sides down, until toasted, about 20 seconds. Rub the toasted sides with the garlic and halved tomato.'),
('4113', '6', 'Cut the baguette pieces crosswise in half and serve right away with the kebabs.'),
('4114', '1', 'In a saucepan over medium-low heat, gently sweat the garlic in the olive oil until it is very soft but not browned.'),
('4114', '2', 'Add the onion and continue cooking 5 to 7 minutes, until the onion is soft and browning. Increase the heat to medium-high and add tomato halves, cut sides down. Cook the tomatoes, turning frequently, until they have released their juices and are very soft.'),
('4114', '3', 'Stir in parsley, red pepper flakes, salt, pepper, and cinnamon, cover the pan and cook for 15 minutes, until the sauce is thick and flavorful.'),
('4114', '4', 'Remove the cinnamon stick and push the sauce through a fine-mesh sieve or vegetable mill or process to a coarse puree. Return the sauce to the rinsed-out pan over medium heat.'),
('4114', '5', 'Cut the monkfish into 6 serving-sized pieces and add to the simmering sauce. Cook, turning the fish pieces until the fish is cooked through but still firm, about 7 to 10 minutes.'),
('4114', '6', 'Remove from heat and serve immediately, spooning sauce over fish pieces.'),
('4116', '1', 'With tongs or a slotted spoon, transfer to paper towels to drain.'),
('4116', '2', 'Return the skillet to medium heat, add the fennel and season with salt and the red pepper flakes. Stir with a wooden spoon to coat the fennel with the oil and pancetta drippings and saute for just a minute or two, until the fennel begins to sizzle.'),
('4116', '3', 'Add 1/4 cup water and stir and scrape the bottom to dislodge and dissolve any tasty cooked-on pancetta bits. Cover, reduce the heat to medium-low, and braise, stirring a few times, until the fennel is tender with just a little resistance, about 7 minutes.'),
('4116', '4', 'Add another tablespoon of oil to the pan, along with the tomatoes and garlic.Increase the heat to medium and saute, uncovered, shaking and stirring frequently, until the tomatoes begin to burst, about 10 minutes. Stir often and scrape up the lovely caramelized crust that will develop on the bottom of the skillet. When about half the tomatoes have burst, about 12 minutes, add another 2 to 3 tablespoons of water and the pancetta, cover, reduce the heat to medium-low and let simmer, stirring occassionally, while you prepare the fish.'),
('4116', '5', 'Inspect the monkfish. Most monkfish comes from the market with a thin grayish, rather slimy membrane covering the fish. This is a natural layer that exists between the skin and the pure white fillet and it should be removed for aesthetic and textural reasons. Some markets trim this for you, but most do not. using a sharp paring knife or fillet knife, trim away the membrane without cutting into the fish. Trim off any dark patches on the monkfish as well.[I actually found it quite difficult to cut away all the dark bits. I did the best I could but, retrospectively, I shouldn''t have stressed so much. the dark bits that remained were fine and mostly obscured by the sauce.]'),
('4116', '6', 'Cut the monkfish fillet into 4 equal portions.'),
('4116', '7', 'Pat the monkfish fillets dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper.'),
('4116', '8', 'Heat the remaining tablespoon of oil in a medium nonstick skillet (9 to 10-inch) over medium high heat. When the oil shimmers, add the fish and saute until it has lost its raw appearance and the outside is pale golden, 4 minutes per side.'),
('4116', '9', 'Transfer the fillets to the simmering tomato-fennel sauce. With a rubber spatula, scrape any oil or juices from the nonstick skillet onto the fillets. Cover and simmer gently over low heat, turning the fillets after 4 minutes, until the fish is just cooked through, about 8 minutes total.'),
('4116', '10', 'Transfer the monkfish to warm plates. Stir the basil into the sauce, taste for salt and pepper and spoon it around the fish on each plate.'),
('4116', '11', 'Serve and enjoy!Tags: braising, fish, Molly Stevens'),
('4116', '12', 'Categories: Recipes, Seafood'),
('4117', '1', 'Heat peanut oil in a large sauce pan over medium heat. Stir in chopped onion, and cook until softened and translucent, 3 to 5 minutes.');